              <title>Training pre-service teachers in the lifelong learning sector - the challenges</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/4864</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/4864</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>Training pre-service teachers in the lifelong learning sector is challenging - inexperienced ones are overwhelmed and experienced ones are blas&eacute;.&nbsp; HE teachers see nothing wrong in delivering long lectures.&nbsp; FE teachers want to focus on classroom management - just get the students to behave, never mind the learning.&nbsp; ACL teachers feel very responsible for their learners - nurturing.</p>
<p>As their teacher educator I have to be constantly creative - my focus is 50% on knowledge and skills and 50% on attitude.</p>
<p>If you also train teachers in this sector - please share your experiences and good practices.</p>]]></description>
